{
  "texts": [
    "Strong amplitude of microlensing has been found in the Fe III multiplet visible in restframe UV (i.e.",
    "range [2039-2113] Å) suggesting that emission arises in the direct vicinity of the disc and in a region almost as compact as the latter (Guerras et al. 2013b; Shalyapin and Goicoechea 2014; Fian et al. 2021a).",
    "By combining the SMBH mass inferred from the redshift and broadening of this line, with microlensing-based estimates of BLR sizes, Mediavilla et al. (2020) constrained the virial factor, f, of several low ionization lines in an ensemble of 10 quasars.",
    "Just a year after the first detection of a microlensing-induced variability in Q 2237+0305 (Irwin et al. 1989), Wambsganss et al. (1990) compared the observed variations to simulated light curves and predicted the Optical-UV size of its accretion disc radius to be < 2 10 15 cm.",
    "This early result showed consistency with the expectations of the thin-disc theory."
  ]
}